Blurb::
Scaling parameter


Description::
Value of parameter :math:`b` in equation for the scaling scalar :math:`a_i` in the :math:`i`-th stage, :math:`i=0,1,...,N-1`, where :math:`N` is the number of stages (parameter 
:dakkw:`method-bayes_calibration-muq-dr_num_stages`). The equation can be either :math:`a_i = b/(i+1)` (in case of :dakkw:`method-bayes_calibration-muq-dr_scale_type` = "Linear")
or :math:`a_i = b/2^i` (for "Power"). Value must be positive. Used by the DR and DRAM MCMC algorithms.

